DeepSeek-V4 EAGLE-MTP marlin branch + TileLang 0.1.8 indexer compat
patch-application steps for container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly.

Adds two COPY+RUN steps to the sglang Python source AFTER the SM121
sgl-kernel patches but BEFORE `uv pip install ./python`, so the installed
package picks up the changes. Same anchor/pattern as the retired
dockerfile-dsv4-nvfp4.patch — but this variant is for v0.5.14+, where
PR #25820's base NVFP4-MoE support is already NATIVE (no longer patched)
and only two GB10-specific remainders are still needed:

Step 1: applies sglang-dsv4-mtp-marlin-v0.5.14.patch (adds the marlin
draft-MoE branch inside the native HybridFp8NvFp4Config.get_quant_method —
without it, EAGLE-MTP's draft MoE hardcodes an SM100-only TVM kernel that
crashes on GB10).

Step 2: applies sglang-tilelang-018-indexer-compat.patch (TileLang 0.1.8
compat fix for the DSA paged-MQA indexer kernel: promotes two 1D shared
buffers to 2D for inject_permuted_layout compat, and adds .view(torch.uint8)
before the kvcache view — required for the SGLANG_OPT_USE_TILELANG_INDEXER
path to compile on TL 0.1.8, unchanged since 0.5.13-sm121).

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly AFTER
dockerfile-sm121.patch has been applied. Application is gated by
build_sm121_image.sh on the recipe variable
APPLY_DSV4_MTP_MARLIN_TILELANG=1 (set in sglang-0.5.14-sm121.recipe).
Remove once both upstream fixes land in the pinned SGLANG_REF / TileLang.

NOTE: anchors on the same Dockerfile region as the retired
dockerfile-dsv4-nvfp4.patch and dockerfile-gemma4-nvfp4.patch (the end of
the sm121-debug block). Regenerate this patch's context if that region
drifts upstream.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -290,6 +290,34 @@
         echo "=== Skipping sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG=${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG}) ==="; \
     fi

+# DeepSeek-V4 EAGLE-MTP draft-MoE marlin routing (SM121/GB10-only fix).
+# HybridFp8NvFp4Config's native NVFP4-MoE dispatch (upstream PR #25820,
+# native since SGLang v0.5.14) hardcodes the MTP/nextn draft MoE layers to
+# an SM100-only TVM kernel that crashes on GB10. This adds a marlin (SM80+)
+# branch selected via --speculative-moe-runner-backend marlin. Gated by
+# build_sm121_image.sh on APPLY_DSV4_MTP_MARLIN_TILELANG=1.
+COPY patches/sglang-dsv4-mtp-marlin-v0.5.14.patch /tmp/sglang-dsv4-mtp-marlin-v0.5.14.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang && \
+    echo "=== Applying sglang-dsv4-mtp-marlin-v0.5.14.patch (MTP marlin branch) ===" && \
+    patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sglang-dsv4-mtp-marlin-v0.5.14.patch && \
+    patch -p1 < /tmp/sglang-dsv4-mtp-marlin-v0.5.14.patch && \
+    grep -q 'Mxfp4MarlinMoEMethod(Fp8MoEMethod(self)' python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/modelopt_quant.py && \
+    echo 'DSV4 MTP marlin patch applied successfully'
+
+# TileLang 0.1.8 compat fix for the DSA paged-MQA indexer kernel.
+# Promotes two 1D shared allocs to 2D (inject_permuted_layout compat) and
+# adds .view(torch.uint8) to the kvcache view. Required for the
+# SGLANG_OPT_USE_TILELANG_INDEXER path to compile on TL 0.1.8 (bundled in
+# both 0.5.13-sm121 and 0.5.14-sm121 images — unchanged file at this
+# function). Validated on GB10/SM121 2026-06-20.
+COPY patches/sglang-tilelang-018-indexer-compat.patch /tmp/sglang-tilelang-018-indexer-compat.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang && \
+    echo "=== Applying sglang-tilelang-018-indexer-compat.patch (TL 0.1.8 compat) ===" && \
+    patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sglang-tilelang-018-indexer-compat.patch && \
+    patch -p1 < /tmp/sglang-tilelang-018-indexer-compat.patch && \
+    grep -q 'TL0.1.8 fix' python/sglang/srt/layers/attention/dsa/tilelang_kernel.py && \
+    echo 'TileLang 0.1.8 compat patch applied successfully'
+
 # Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch).
 # Moved here from its original early-stage location so the installed
 # dist-packages picks up the patched nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh above.
